                            <comment id="424920" author="adilger" created="Sat, 17 Aug 2024 00:41:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is actually an error after the IGNORE if the copy is &lt;b&gt;too&lt;/b&gt; slow:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt; sanity test_56xk: @@@@@@ FAIL: &apos;lfs mirror resync -W&apos; too slow in VM (19 &amp;gt; 3.5 * 5)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure what would be the best way to handle this, since I think the issue is mostly test VM related.  One option is to increase the &quot;slow&quot; margins (e.g. 3.5x for the &lt;tt&gt;error_not_in_vm&lt;/tt&gt; and 8x for &lt;tt&gt;error&lt;/tt&gt;, and another option is to retry the test run a few times if it is a VM to see if it is persistently slow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These measures will also not be perfect, but at least reduce the false positive rate significantly so that when there are failures they will be more noticeable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
